servings: 2
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}.

Fry until the mince has browned and the mushrooms are cooked, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the mince cooks, pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to a boil.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt
and @pepper. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @Szechuan paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{50%g} and @soy sauce{25%ml}.

Stir the cooked noodles into the sauce. Taste and season with @salt and @pepper
if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if the sauce is looking a little too thick.

Share your Szechuan beef noodles between your #serving bowls{}.
Enjoy!